title: Texas Republican Governor Greg Abbott defeats Beto O’Rourke, re-elected for third term
description: Texas Gov. Greg Abbott will remain as governor for a third term, defeating Democrat Beto O’Rourke, the Fox News Decision Desk projects.

title: Maricopa County: Arizona judge denies GOP lawsuit to keep polls open in county after ballot 'hiccups'
description: An Arizona judge declined to keep polls open in Maricopa County, Arizona, after the scheduled 7 p.m. MT closing time despite a lawsuit from Republicans.

title: Texas police say two dead in shooting at Dallas County Medical Examiner's Office
description: Two people died in a shooting on Tuesday at the Dallas County Medical Examiner's Office, including an employee

title: Oklahoma Gov. Kevin Stitt finds himself in surprisingly tough re-election campaign against Joy Hofmeister
description: Oklahoma Gov. Kevin Stitt is having a harder time than expected in his re-election campaign against Joy Hofmeister. Hofmeister has been blasting Stitt for his education spending plan.

title: Fox News Voter Analysis: Most voters dissatisfied or angry with government
description: In Georgia, voters say the balance of power in the Senate will shape their vote; more than half in the state say it's the single most important consideration.

title: Illinois Democratic Gov. JB Pritzker reelected, defeats Republican Darren Bailey
description: Democratic Illinois Gov. JB Pritzker won a second term by defeating Republican challenger Darren Bailey in the state's gubernatorial race on Tuesday.

title: North Carolina's 13th District, state's lone swing district, may affect control of Congress
description: North Carolina's 13th District is expected to play a role in determining which party has control of Congress. It is unclear whether the state will remain red due to redistricting.

title: Dabo Swinney threatens to bench starting QB if it will improve Clemson's offensive woes
description: Clemson head coach Dabo Swinney openly acknowledged that benching his starting quarterback is on the table amid his quest to fix the Tigers struggling offense.

title: Arkansas governor: Republican Sarah Huckabee Sanders defeats Chris Jones
description: Former White House Press Secretary Sarah Huckabee Sanders is projected to win the Arkansas gubernatorial race, defeating Democrat Chris Jones.

title: In Pennsylvania, Oz, Fetterman reach home stretch of exhausting Senate race
description: Pennsylvania's Senate race between Dr. Mehmet Oz and Lt. Gov. John Fetterman nears its end, with both candidates having seen a tumultuous campaign in the lead-up.

title: Warnock, Walker hope for outright Georgia Senate victory, must surpass 50% threshold
description: Georgia's Senate contest between Herschel Walker and Raphael Warnock may not be determined Tuesday night. If neither candidate surpasses 50% of votes, it would set up a Dec. 6 runoff.

title: Florida's Miami-Dade County turns red for DeSantis: First GOP gov to win in two decades
description: Miami-Dade County in South Florida supported Gov. Ron DeSantis and Sen. Marco Rubio as Republicans aim to take control of Congress.

title: CFP Top 25: TCU breaks into top four, Tennessee doesn't fall far after loss to Georgia
description: The latest College Football Playoff rankings are out and TCU has cracked the top four after remaining undefeated this week and Tennessee (No. 5) falling to Georgia (No. 1).

title: Twitter users knock MSNBC analyst for casting doubts on Georgia election: 'Denialism, man'
description: Twitter users hit MSNBC analyst Jason Johnson’s comments on "Deadline: White House" casting doubts on the accuracy of Georgia’s midterm elections Tuesday night.

title: NPR panned for AZ race slant: 'Election denying' Kari Lake versus Katie Hobbs 'defending election integrity'
description: NPR faced backlash on social media for its slanted headline covering the Arizona gubernatorial race between Republican Kari Lake and Democrat Katie Hobbs.

title: Emily Ratajkowski says she bought 1-year-old son a baby doll and tea set to 'balance out' his 'love' of trucks
description: Emily Ratajkowski said she recently bought her 1-year-old son Sly, whom she shares with ex Sebastian Bear-McLard, a baby doll and tea set to "balance out" toys he likes.

title: Ron DeSantis defeats Charlie Crist in closely watched Florida gubernatorial race
description: Fox News Decision Desk projects that Republican Gov. Ron DeSantis will defeat Democrat Charlie Crist to secure another term as the Sunshine State's chief executive.

title: Florida Senate: GOP Sen. Marco Rubio defeats Democratic challenger Rep. Val Demings
description: GOP Sen. Marco Rubio has defeated Democratic challenger Rep. Val Demings in the 2022 midterm race to retain his position in the Florida Senate.

title: MA Democratic AG Healey and Trump-endorsed Republican Diehl battle for governor in heated race
description: Voters in Massachusetts are being presented with two vastly different candidates for governor, Democrat Maura Healey and Republican Geoff Diehl, in a heated gubernatorial race.

title: Michigan officials say everyone was able to vote in Detroit after 'harmless data error'
description: Michigan officials denied former President Trump's claim that some voters had been turned away in Detroit after a 'harmless data error.'

title: NASA moves Artemis I launch date due to approaching Tropical Storm Nicole
description: Nasa is skipping Monday's launch attempt of its new moon rocket over concerns about a Tropical Storm headed to Florida that could become a hurricane.

title: Giants' Xavier McKinney explains 'freak accident' that left him with broken fingers
description: New York Giants safety Xavier McKinney said that he has no timeline for his return after an ATV crash during the bye week left him with broken fingers.

title: Midterm malaise: Biden, Democrats may be losing both voters and the media, critics say
description: President Joe Biden was given a "bottomless Pinocchio" rating for a recent claim; issued by the Washington Post's longtime fact-checker, Glenn Kessler.

title: NM's Lujan Grisham faces re-election challenge with crime, abortion and spending on ballot
description: Democrat New Mexico Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham faces a competitive re-election battle against former KRQE meteorologist Mark Ronchetti, in a race driven by crime and economic concerns.

title: Democrat Wes Moore hoping to make Maryland history as state's first Black governor
description: Wes Moore, the Democratic gubernatorial candidate in Maryland, is looking to become the state's first Black governor. Rep. Anthony Brown is running to be the state's first Black AG.

title: NYT advises readers to 'breathe like a baby' to help 'cope' with election 'stress:' 'You cannot be serious'
description: The New York Times was widely mocked for telling readers to 'breathe like a baby' to cope with Election Day "anxiety" in a social media post released late Tuesday.

title: Lamar Jackson makes young fan's day with huge surprise
description: Landon Berry, who suffers from a heart condition, got the surprise of a lifetime when his idol, Lamar Jackson, visited him and his family before the Ravens' win on Monday.

title: Maricopa County: Blake Masters, Kari Lake and RNC sue after 'hiccups' at Arizona voting locations
description: The Republican National Committee and campaigns for Arizona's two major statewide GOP candidates are suing Maricopa County over voting machine 'hicccups.'

title: MA voters decide on millionaire tax, driver's licenses for those in country illegally
description: Massachusetts voters will decide whether illegal immigrants in the state can obtain a driver's license and whether to impose a 4% surtax on the incomes of millionaires in the midterms.

title: Jeff Cook, co-founder of Alabama, dead at 73
description: Jeff Cook, a guitarist and co-founder of country band Alabama, has died. Fox News Digital confirmed Cook died in Destin, Florida, Monday at the age of 73.

title: Voters in South Dakota to decide on Medicaid expansion to low-income residents in midterms
description: Voters in South Dakota will decide if the state constitution should be amended to expand Medicaid health insurance for low-income residents.

title: Passenger's reclined plane seat seen in TikTok video reawakens debate: 'Bane of my existence'
description: TikTok users are divided on whether reclining seats on a plane is rude after a video shared by The Pointer Brothers shows a leaned-back seat hovering over a meal tray.

title: Liberal CNN analyst declares Democrats have lived in an 'ivory tower' for too long
description: Bakari Sellers, a former Democrat member of the South Carolina House of Representatives, slammed Democrats Tuesday for living "for too long" in "an ivory tower."

title: Tom Brady calls Bucs' effort on game day 'embarrassing': 'Something we better fix'
description: Tom Brady said Monday the "most embarrassing" part of the Tamp Bay Buccaneers is their game-day effort, and added that it's something "we better fix."

title: Lainey Wilson details what it’s like filming ‘Yellowstone,’ being recognized after 11 years in country music
description: Singer-songwriter Lainey Wilson discussed her guest appearance on season 5 of "Yellowstone" and how excited she is to be nominated for six CMA Awards.
